# migrated from tests/cases/repair.it.chat (aligned to current behaviour)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test repair.it]
# gen141 (E2), Italian probe: the repair loop reaches the SAME code path through
# canonicalize_lang. The Italian subject pronoun "esso" maps to "it", so a cold
# referential gap opens the same clarification and resumes the same way — the
# competence lives in the mechanism, not an English-only surface (LOOP.md ratchet).

# A fresh question instead of an answer expires the pending repair.
# gen335 (KB-first): identity responses localize via current_language.
> è esso un cane?
< Who or what does "it" refer to?
> chi sei?
< Mi chiamo parrot0.

# Knowledge gap opened in Italian, resolved by an Italian teaching answer: the
# stored pronoun then resolves by coreference and the original question is
# answered for real.
> ogni cane è un mammifero
< Learned rule: mammifero(X) :- dog(X).
> è esso un mammifero?
< Who or what does "it" refer to?
> rex è un cane
< Yes.
